<meta name="description" content="Years ago the machinist appreciated a good cold chisel. He had to do all his heavy planing and shaping with them, and he took care to have the best and keep them in shape. If a man was going to chip the teeth of a big bevel gear, in order to remove the scale, he would be pretty apt to look around for the very best cold chisels he could get hold of, and then he would keep them sharp.">

